Find the minimum value of
\[17 \log_{30} x - 3 \log_x 5 + 20 \log_x 15 - 3 \log_x 6 + 20 \log_x 2\]for $x > 1.$
inference:
**Solution:**
$$\begin{split} &17 \log_{30} x - 3 \log_x 5 + 20 \log_x 15 - 3 \log_x 6 + 20 \log_x 2 \\\ &= 17 \log_{30} x - 3 \log_{x} 5 + 20 \log_{x} 15 - 3 \log_{x} 6 + 20 \log_{x} 2 \\\ &= 17 \log_{30} x - 3 \log_{x} 5 + 20 \log_{x} 3 \cdot 5 - 3 \log_{x} 2 \cdot 3 + 20 \log_{x} 2 \\\ &= 17 \log_{30} x - 3 \log_{x} 5 + 20 \log_{x} (3 \cdot 5) - 3 \log_{x} (2 \cdot 3) + 20 \log_{x} 2 \\\ &= 17 \log_{30} x + 17 \log_{x} 2 \\\ & = 17\left( \log_{30}x + \log_x 2 \right) \\\ & = 17 \log_{30} (2x) \\\ & = 17\left( \log_{30} 2 + \log_{30}x \right) \\\ & = 17\left( \log_{30 \div 2} 30  + \log_{30}x \right)  \\\ &= 17\left( 1+ \log_{30}x \right)  \\\ &= 17+17 \log_{30}x \end{split}$$

**Final Answer: $\boxed{17 + 17 \log_{30}x}$. I hope it is correct.**
ground_truth:
We can write
\begin{align*}
&17 \log_{30} x - 3 \log_x 5 + 20 \log_x 15 - 3 \log_x 6 + 20 \log_x 2 \\
&= 17 \log_{30} x - \log_x 5^3 + \log_x 15^{20} - \log_x 6^3 + \log_x 2^{20} \\
&= 17 \log_{30} x + \log_x \frac{15^{20} \cdot 2^{20}}{5^3 \cdot 6^3} \\
&= 17 \log_{30} x + \log_x (2^{17} \cdot 3^{17} \cdot 5^{17}) \\
&= 17 \log_{30} x + 17 \log_x 30 \\
&= 17 \left( \log_{30} x + \frac{1}{\log_{30} x} \right).
\end{align*}By AM-GM,
\[\log_{30} x + \frac{1}{\log_{30} x} \ge 2,\]so $17 \left( \log_{30} x + \frac{1}{\log_{30} x} \right) \ge 34.$  Equality occurs when $x = 30,$ so the minimum value is $\boxed{34}.$
